{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5aa46cc2-24c7-4f94-afa6-bd067350c11e","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Replace all image tags\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0\n```\n\n**Then:**\n- Install the .NET 11 SDK locally.\n- Run `dotnet restore` to pull updated packages.\n- Check for any NuGet packages with a `.NET 10`-specific version (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) and bump them to their `11.x` equivalents.\n- Run `dotnet build` and `dotnet test` to verify everything compiles and passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"df3dfa29-53ba-4256-90a1-baf2f945c36f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward guidance question — I don't need to explore any codebase since they've described their setup. Let me provide concise instructions.","outputTokens":329,"requestId":"6824:2A6ECB:5C7455E:656149B:69F010E1"},"id":"9be4bb4a-934a-4d6b-8916-b46120688379","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:44:09.571Z","parentId":"1d2b18f1-6533-4150-937c-30f12fd8eb79"}
